 at $z\\sim~0.5-1.0$ the main galaxy quenching mode depends on its already\nformed stellar mass, exhibiting a transition from \"the outside-in\" at $M_{\\ast}\n\\leq 10^{10}M_{\\odot}$ to \"the inside-out\" at $M_{\\ast} > 10^{10.5}M_{\\odot}$.\nIn other words, our findings support that internal processes dominate the\nquenching of massive galaxies, whereas external processes dominate the\nquenching of low-mass galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 May 2018 01:37:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-27"}
